race.comment: REBELNADO (1) was a touch slow into stride last start but it didn't matter as he ran over the top to win impressively at Pinjarra. He was only second-up there and suspect further improvement is on the cards now. Back slightly in trip shouldn't pose an issue and he can go back-to-back. ALMAYA (2) disappointed last start at Pinjarra but was in much better form prior to that. He has enough early speed to offset the barrier and coming back to a CL2 is a big tick. Can sit handy and bounce back to winning ways. MISTER POPCORN (3) has gotten a long way back in both runs this time in, but has finished off well under Hearn who remains in the saddle. Third-up now and out to a more suitable trip, he can improve on what he's done thus far. Looks a key player. GINGERQUEST (5) creates interest as he steps out to this trip for the first time. Can surprise. LORDGIVEMESTRENGTH (7) can improve following a disappointing effort most recently.
